transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, hi, my name is Peter Doering. I have a prescription with you, I guess. I got something in the mail, and I don't know how it happened. I want to make sure it's going to stop.

Speaker 1: Do you need an Rx number?

Speaker 2: Give me just a moment.

Speaker 1: And what was your last name, sir?

Speaker 2: My last name is Doering, spelled D-E-A-R-I-N-G.

Speaker 1: First name?

Speaker 2: Peter.

Speaker 1: Okay, Peter, and you said you wanted to get this thing stopped?

Speaker 2: Well, quite frankly, I don't know how it happened. I got some shipment in the other day.

Speaker 1: You got an order and it just kept coming?

Speaker 2: Excuse me?

Speaker 1: You got an order and a few more just showed up?

Speaker 2: Well, I don't really recall, to tell you the truth. So I got this without realizing it was coming. I don't really need any more.

Speaker 1: I don't know, have you been charging me for this?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you definitely were charged for it, $63.95.

Speaker 1: $63.95, that's ridiculous.

Speaker 2: I can get these through my – go ahead.

Speaker 1: I mean, if you don't want to keep it, you definitely can send it back.

Speaker 2: I can pause the account for you if you did want to place orders in the future.

Speaker 1: You should be getting our new Viagra AGB, which other doctors definitely aren't able to prescribe.

Speaker 2: We're the only FDA-approved vendor of that medicine, but that's neither here nor there.

Speaker 1: But if you want, like I said, I can pause it for you, Peter.

Speaker 2: If you did want to cancel, I can help you out with that as well.

Speaker 1: I just won't be able to fill these orders from you.

Speaker 2: I want to cancel.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: I can help you out with that.

Speaker 1: I just won't be able to fill these orders from you in the future.

Speaker 2: And like I said, we are the only FDA-approved company that gets these pills from Pfizer.

Speaker 1: Hold on, hold on, hold on.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry.

Speaker 1: Yeah, kind of hard to hear and I can't hear you well.

Speaker 2: You can or cannot cancel for me?

Speaker 1: I can, of course.

Speaker 2: But I was letting you know, we are the only FDA-approved company that sells this medicine.

Speaker 1: So if you get it from your doctor, it could be coming from China or India or something.

Speaker 2: So I just want to make you aware before I finalize the cancel for you.

Speaker 1: Yes, I'm aware of that.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: So I'm taking care of that for you now.

Speaker 1: And you are all set.

Speaker 2: You're not going to get anything else.

Speaker 1: Okay, Peter?

Speaker 2: Is there any way to get a confirming email or something on that?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can send you a confirmation email.

Speaker 2: That's no problem.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you'll see that come by in just the next minute or so.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: All righty, thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Enjoy the rest of your day.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye now.

Speaker 2: Okay, take care.

Speaker 1: Bye.
